resources.description:
## Purpose
	
API which allows to get the list of sessions and events in a specified timeframe. Request must be made ***always*** in UTC time.
Data will contain only events.


## Authentication method (Bearer token)

Authentication can be achieved by using the ``acces_token`` in the Header of REST request, such as:

	'Authorization': 'Bearer ' + server.access_token

## Input data

* from: start time (ex: 20210222110000)
* to: end time (ex: 20210222110000)
* SearchMode:  if using "lastUpdate" it will search using the last update parameters of the DB
* limit : limit the output list (if search is greater than this value, excess will not be sent)

## Responses

The operation will provide a JSON object named ***result*** which contains the status of the request.

Possible output codes are:
```
"OPERATION_SUCCEDED" = 0
"INVALID_SERVER" = 1
"LOGIN_FAILURE" = 2
"LOGOUT_FAILURE" = 3
"USERS_ALREADY_LOGGED_IN" = 4
"NO_USER_LOGGED_IN_SESSION_IS_NOT_VALID" = 5
"CAMERA_IS_NOT_A_DOME_PTZ" = 6
"INVALID_PIN" = 7
"SERVER_OFFLINE" = 8
"INVALID_QUERY_STRING" = 9
"SERVER_CONNECTION_ERROR" = 10
"NOT_SUPPORTED" = 11
"INPUT_DATA_ARE_NOT_VALID" = 12
"PLAY_RECORDINGS_REQUEST_FAILURE" = 13
"NO_START_TIME_PROVIDED" = 14
"NO_END_TIME_PROVIDED" = 15

```

resources.description:
## Purpose
	
API which allows to get the list of sessions and events in a specified timeframe. Request must be made ***always*** in UTC time. Data will contain both servers’ sessions and servers’ events.
Data will contain both servers sessions and server events.

## Authentication method (Bearer token)

Authentication can be achieved by using the ``acces_token`` in the Header of REST request, such as:

	'Authorization': 'Bearer ' + server.access_token

## Input data

* from: start time (ex: 20210222110000)
* to: end time (ex: 20210222110000)
* SearchMode: if using "lastUpdate" it will search using the last update parameters of the DB
* limit : limit the output list (if search is greater than this value, excess will not be sent)

## Responses

The operation will provide a JSON object named ***result*** which contains the status of the request.

resources.description:
## Purpose

Send a live event to Arteco directly to an Arteco Channel.

## Authentication method (Bearer token)

Authentication can be achieved by using the ``acces_token`` in the Header of REST request, such as:

	'Authorization': 'Bearer ' + server.access_token

This API, by default, is protected. It is possible to disable it by changing the Arteco Backend configuration that can be found inside the Arteco-Server folder.
The file is inside ``\Arteco-backend`` and it's called ``BackendConfig.json``.
Changing the protectedEventCreation to 'false' will disable the authentication of the API.

❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗❗

```json
{
  "port":9007,
  "socketServerPort":9008,
  "socketGatewayPort":71,
  "protectedEventCreation":false
}
```

## Input data

Input data must be sent as a JSON body.

* chId: channel Id
* param: event description
* brand: brand of the integrator
* data: JSON object with data
* image: base64 image (string must contain ```data:image/jpeg;base64``` at the begin)
* cat: category of the event

```json
	"lane": "manageEvent",
````

API which allows to get the list of sessions and events in a specified timeframe. Request must be made ***always*** in UTC time.

## Input data

* SessionId : Id of the current session
* from: start time (ex: 20210222110000)
* to: end time (ex: 20210222110000)
* devIds: list of peripherals ids
* chIds: list of channels ids
* eventsCat: lis of categories
* queryParams: string to be lloking for
* SearchMode: if using "lastUpdate" it will searching using the last update parameters of the DB
* outfmt : output format that could be XML or JSON (if omitted is JSON)

## Responses

The operation will provide a JSON object named ***result*** which contains the status of the request.

Possible output codes are:

API which allows to request the HLS stream of a recorded stream

## Input data

* SessionId : Id of the current session
* chId : id of the camera
* dvr : stream (main or sub)
* from : start time of the UTC request
* to : end time of the UTC request
* outfmt : output format that could be XML or JSON (if omitted is JSON)

## Responses

The operation will provide a JSON object named ***result*** which contains the status of the request.
